Faction Feud - The Baseball Club Panics
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Activity Logs - Disbanded Club & School Reputation

<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High is one of Kyushu's
top preparatory schools.
It focuses on both academics and
extracurricular activities.
The school's sport clubs regularly perform
well at tournaments.

In particular, the baseball club is the school's pride and joy.
They flourish on the national stage every year,
and were the runner-up at last year's
national tournament.

<FUL:SAKURAZAKI>, the notorious problem
child of <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.
A stain on the school's good name...
Some call him scum and wish he would drop out.
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High no longer has a football club.\nFor some reason, the club was disbanded,\nand all records of why have been erased.
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI> got into another fight!\nThe thug he kicked went flying through the air.\nWhat training's he doing for his legs to get that strong?

This problem child played football once...
It fits that a messy sport like football was his choice.

Delinquent's Shocking History
<FUL:SAKURAZAKI> was once wholeheartedly devoted
to football and never missed a day of practice...

Since when does a middle schooler fight
genuine gangsters?!
Talk about an adolescent who either knows no fear,
or has given up on life!

<FUL:SAKURAZAKI> is heir to <LST:SAKURAZAKI> Inc.,
one of the financial supporters of the school,
so he receives special treatment.
Power is a despicable thing.
<FUL:UMIBOZU> statues appear all over <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nSeen as lucky charms and warding off evil,\nthey're usually found in busy spots.

A worn-out football left unused.
Football has been banned at
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High for five years,
making this ball a relic of the past.

A massive tree at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High,
which the students have dubbed the God Tree.
Legend says if you confess your love here unseen,
it will come true.

The baseball club is the pride of
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High.
Regulars at nationals and
ranked among the top schools,
many students enroll just to join the team.
Since the new gym storage opened,\nthe old one's fallen into ruin.\nThe equipment inside is all abandoned and unused.
The building includes a music room,\na multimedia room, a co-op store, and a cafeteria.\nIt boasts the nicest facilities of any junior high.
The baseball club's dedicated storage.\nPersonal items are banned,\nbut footballs used in performances are kept here.
The storage used to store a variety of sports\nequipment. Many clubs argue over its usage.
An old gym storage now a forgotten relic.\nIt's filled with discarded gear,\nbut could be put to good use with some tidying.
Mostly rooms for cultural clubs.\nEvery now and then,\nnoisy and quiet clubs clash over volume.
A hospital staffed with skilled doctors,\ntrusted by the townsfolk.
Modeled after two dolphins that washed ashore\na few years ago, "Doll" and "Finn."\nTheir arrival caused quite a stir.
Trains rarely pass here, but strange sightings\nsometimes spark local urban legends.
A park where neighborhood kids gather to play.\nAlso a favorite hangout for stray cats.
Mostly home to sports clubs,\nthis building sometimes hosts fiery clashes\nbetween its passionate members.
Dance contest champion, <FUL:RAIKA>—\nSome stake out the club just to watch her move.\nBut word is, she never actually shows up...

A ghost member with unmatched pull—
Though listed on the club's roster,
she's been absent from activities
and now drifts as a ghost in name alone.
Undisputed star of the dance club—\nEven if she skips, no one scolds her.\nHer skills and results speak for themselves.

The school idol lost in thought—
<FFC:RAIKA>, a sophomore, was seen on the rooftop,
quietly gazing out over the town.
What could she be doing up there?

The dance club owes it all to <FFC:RAIKA>—
Her popularity is overwhelming.
Truthfully, its success
would be unthinkable without her.

Could she be from a shinobi clan—?
They say a mansion in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>
houses the descendants of real ninja.
And her name is <LST:RAIKA>...

A hot topic across town—
Locals were eager to see whether the new building
would go to the football or baseball club.
The whole town was watching with bated breath.

A club that lived up to its name—
When equipment came crashing down in storage,
the football club rushed in to clean it up.
They proved their reputation wasn't just talk.

Guardians of campus order—
When other students skipped cleanup duty,
the football club stepped in and handled it.
Proof that they were truly dedicated.

A lawless conflict—
The new facility controversy grew by the day,
dragging in students and parents alike.
What started as a club dispute became a full-blown feud.

A tense atmosphere—
The football and baseball clubs were at odds
over the new school building.
Given the surrounding events,
no outcome could possibly satisfy both sides.
Which club truly represents <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High?—\nEven the parents joined in on the rivalry,\nmaking things harder for students caught in the middle.
The football club had the upper hand—\nWith their solid reputation, support kept growing.\nThe baseball club, seeing the tide turn, began to panic.

Unease spread throughout the town—
The faction feud sparked by the new facility controversy
cast a long shadow over daily life,
prompting many residents to demand a swift resolution.
The new facility controversy was resolved—\nAfter the incident, the baseball club got the building,\nbringing the town-wide faction feud to an unexpected close.

Restoring the school's reputation—
After the football club was dissolved, teachers
have continued removing articles about the incident.
It's clear they still have a tough job.

The school's image—
Following the football club's incident,
the faction feud ended. While the outcome was favorable,
one can't help but wonder if this was truly the right resolution.

The Going-Home Club's human observation logs—
The football club was seen talking with the council,
after which they left in high spirits.
Did something good happen?

The handling of important documents—
The Archive houses many critical records managed by
the student council. Handle with care.
Permission must be obtained before viewing any documents.

That classic, old-school flavor—
A must-try when you're in Nagasaki.
They even shape it like a rose—so cute!
I'm curious about other flavors...
But I'll stick with the plain one today.

The legs that carry Nagasaki—
Lovingly called Ting-a-ling Trains by locals,
these trams have run over 100 years.
They carry locals and tourists
day and night, without a fuss.

A land of bent-tailed cats—
Said to come from Edo days,
when trade ships brought cats aboard
to keep mice off the cargo.
Some stayed—and multiplied.

A city built on slopes—
Nagasaki's wrapped in mountains,
so homes perch on steep hillsides.
It's a maze of stairways and alleys—
beautiful, but a real workout!

<MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s grumpy guardian—
"Pollute the sea and it'll gobble you up!"
Every local's heard the tale.
Look around and you'll spot one—
<FUL:UMIBOZU> statues all over town.

A series of wooden cottages for teams visiting
from afar. They're equipped with full-range of
amenities to ensure comfort, including a meeting
hall and combined kitchen-dining area.
The gateway to the Odaiba Football Gardens.\nConveniently located for easy access across Kanto—\nand to the stadium.

The Football Gardens feature four standard pitches,
along with a variety of other fields—including
bowl-shaped and roofed ones—offering a wide range
of playing environments.
A central area in the Soccer Garden with easy access to all zones. \nIts calm atmosphere makes it a popular spot for players to cool down after training.

The heart of the Football Gardens,
granting access to all areas.
Its calm, open atmosphere makes it
a favorite spot for players to relax.

A statue of <FUL:ENDO>, the legendary
football player. Located in the park by
the lodging cottages, a favorite photo spot
for players and fans alike.
A dedicated terminal for traveling between the\nOdaiba Football Gardens and the players' schools.\nThe Skycraft holds around twenty passengers.

A popular spot known for its open, spacious
design, featuring foodstalls, convenience stores,
and souvenir shops. It's also a favorite hangout
for players between matches.
A practice ground built with the baseball wing.\nThe top-tier equipment speaks volumes\nabout the expectations for the baseball club.
The baseball club's own building,\nbuilt several years ago. It has a gym, showers,\nand all the facilities a top club demands.
A standard school pool,\nfitted with a water circulation\nand purification system to keep students healthy.
Originally an equipment shed,\nit was converted into a dedicated dance club room\nthanks to their impressive achievements.
A practice building for the marine biology club.\nIt's surrounded by ponds for raising fish, and inside,\nequipment recreates ocean habitats.

A long-loved shopping street in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.
Plans for a castle-shaped mall have surfaced,
but most locals oppose it
because it would spoil the view.
A local shop selling daily goods and groceries.\nThough the selection is limited,\nit meets locals' needs and is always busy.
This is the home of <FUL:OJIRO>,\nfounder of <LST:OJIRO> Inc. Despite owning it,\nhis busy schedule means he seldom returns.

<MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s key transit hub,
served by lines like the No. 9 West Line.
The station's beautiful gothic design
faces a large roundabout lined with shops.
A burger chain with locations all over Nagasaki.\nKnown for hearty portions,\nit's a popular local favorite and regional staple.
A letter-shaped monument at <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Port,\nperfect for photos. Tourists love it,\nand locals say it shines brightest at sunset.
Once a thriving naval port,\nnow a bustling hub for trade and business,\nwith plenty of coastal amenities to enjoy.
Beyond the downtown arcade lies this pitch,\nbuilt to boost local health.\nAlso home base for the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Shopkeepers.
This old shipyard is set for demolition.\nA seafood processing plant is planned,\nbut funding delays have put it on hold.
The lighthouse by the beach near the lodgings\nhas long stood guard,\nguiding ships safely with its timeless light.
